Support remote docker hosts on OS X.

This commit brings two main changes, notably:

Two new options that can be set as environment variables

- DOCKER_OPTS: any arbitrary set of docker options. Example: --tlsverify
- DOCKER_NATIVE: This forces the use of the native docker available.
                 This is most useful if you're on OS X and do not want
                 to use boot2docker.

Now uses 'docker cp' instead of tar piping to transfer files. This
currently must be done by copying the binaries off of the docker volume
and into a local filesystem (/tmp) before a docker cp is done. This
workaround will no longer be necessary after bug fix
https://github.com/docker/docker/pull/8509 makes it into stable.

This was necessary because the tar | tar method was creating corrupted
archives on OS X even with the < /dev/null workaround.

Support remote docker hosts on OS X.

This commit brings two main changes, notably:

Two new options that can be set as environment variables

- DOCKER_OPTS: any arbitrary set of docker options. Example: --tlsverify
- DOCKER_NATIVE: This forces the use of the native docker available.
                 This is most useful if you're on OS X and do not want
                 to use boot2docker.

Now uses 'docker cp' instead of tar piping to transfer files. This
currently must be done by copying the binaries off of the docker volume
and into a local filesystem (/tmp) before a docker cp is done. This
workaround will no longer be necessary after bug fix
https://github.com/docker/docker/pull/8509 makes it into stable.

This was necessary because the tar | tar method was creating corrupted
archives on OS X even with the < /dev/null workaround.

archives on OS X even with the < /dev/null workaround.

commit_list.message: Issue-31 Resolves issue #31

Updates dev environment with monit node.

Also addresses the following issues:

- resolves #23 monitor node included in demo now
- resolves #22 disks managed directly by vagrant now.

Updated documentation to use sphinx-doc.

Also added a few generated files to the .gitignore

Updated documentation for apps changes.

Docs not cover the new application naming conventions and tasks.
Corrects app name in local demo template.
Fixes syntax error in apps:clean.

Demo overhaul and validation

- Added gitignore entries for miscellaneous untracked files
- Updated ruby version to 2.1.2 (should work!)
- Added rbenv-gemsets for rbenv's
- Renamed rst files for all lowercase for consistency with underscore
  naming conventions
- Added all *.rst files to rake doc:build task
- Added images of expected vbox network configuration for verification
- Also added to gitignore and the exclude list for the tar occam archive.
- Moved demo operations into rake tasks.
- Vagrantfile is now templatized in lib/tempates
- Added a lib/helpers library
- Added a lib/tasks/demo.rake task list
- Added required Gems.
- Added default constants to Rakefile
- rake demo:init now completes _all_ demo tasks up to and including the
  initial puppet run on the ops node.
- Includes a working set of demo local hiera files
  A working set of hiera files are now in lib/files/exmples/demo/local.
  The files are copied into the #{ROOT}/local directory for use during
  demo:init. If an existing set of local files is found, they are left
  alone. The user is warned that their custom locals may not work with the
  demo.
- Added a validation task. Attempts to validate essential components in the
  environment for running the demo.
- Apps are now checked out from github with rake apps:init task. This
  requries a new naming convention. Apps are to be named
  github_username/occam-$appname. So the havana-cloud app would be named
  att-innovate/occam-havana-cloud and would be checked out into the
  puppet/apps/havana-cloud directory.
- Added rake apps:clean command that will remove the specified app or
  all mananged apps. e.g. rake apps:clean[havana-cloud] will remove the
  havana-cloud app.

Updated documentation with community section.

Added reference to Freenode IRC channel.
